Diani Forest, NW & NE within 1km N. of turn oof from new road for Jadini hotel, W. & E. of this road. Areas SW & SE within 1.5km. S. of this point. Recently elevated coral with little soil in its interstices. Dry evergreen forest. Ferns and epiphytic orchids absent. Leguminosae scarce. Common combretum schumannii; frequent Adansonia digitata, Ficus spp., Xylopia holstii, Fagara spp.; occasional Majidea, Bivinia, Balanites wilsonii, Sapindaceae, Tappura, Pleucostylia, Turraea, Tamarindus, Erythrina sacleuxii, Carpodiptera, Harrisonia, Grewia holstii, Milletia usaramensis, Vepris, Allophyllus, Bridelia, Nectaropetalum, Hugonia, Commiphora africana, C.madagascariensis & several Annonaceae.
